1 (a) There is created the Vermont Municipal Response and Recovery
2 Special Fund that shall be managed in accordance with 32 V.S.A. chapter 7,
3 subchapter 5. Annually, 0.5 percent of General Fund revenue shall be
4 deposited and credited to the Special Fund. Notwithstanding 32 V.S.A.
5 § 588(3), all interest earned on Special Fund balances shall be credited to the
6 Special Fund. The State Treasurer may accept gifts, donations, and grants
7 from any source, public or private, to be dedicated for deposit into the Special
8 Fund. Monies in the Special Fund shall be used solely for direct support and
9 assistance to qualifying municipalities for flood response, recovery, and
10 resiliency projects and for necessary costs incurred in administering the Fund.
11 (b) Monies in the Special Fund shall not be disbursed prior to July 1, 2026.
12 Sec. 2. STATE TREASURER; REPORT ON USE OF VERMONT
13 MUNICIPAL RESPONSE AND RECOVERY SPECIAL FUND
14 On or before December 1, 2025, the State Treasurer shall submit a written
15 report to the House Committee on Government Operations and Military
16 Affairs and the Senate Committee on Government Operations concerning:
17 (1) proposed uses and limitations for the Vermont Municipal Response
18 and Recovery Special Fund;
19 (2) guidelines on how Special Fund monies may be distributed to
20 achieve geographic equity and a balance between flood response and
21 mitigation projects;
